## Performance Budget Guidelines (1-20ms targets)

Establishing clear performance budgets ensures your OpenMaui application delivers a consistently smooth user experience. These budgets provide concrete targets for each phase of the rendering pipeline.

## The Frame Budget Breakdown

For 60 FPS (16.67ms per frame), allocate time across pipeline stages:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Frame Budget: 16.67ms                                │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ Event Processing:        2ms  (12%)                 │
│ Layout (Measure/Arrange): 3ms  (18%)                 │
│ Rendering (Skia):        8ms  (48%)                 │
│ GPU Upload/Present:      2ms  (12%)                 │
│ Buffer:                  1.67ms (10%)                │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Per-Operation Budgets

### Event Processing (Target: <2ms)

```csharp
public class EventBudget
{
    // Input event handling
    public const double PointerEvent = 0.5;      // ms
    public const double GestureRecognition = 0.5; // ms
    public const double HitTesting = 0.5;         // ms
    public const double EventDispatch = 0.5;      // ms

    public static void ValidateEventPerformance(string operation, double elapsed)
    {
        var budget = operation switch
        {
            "PointerEvent" => PointerEvent,
            "GestureRecognition" => GestureRecognition,
            "HitTesting" => HitTesting,
            "EventDispatch" => EventDispatch,
            _ => 0.5
        };

        if (elapsed > budget)
        {
            Debug.WriteLine($"⚠️ Budget exceeded: {operation} took {elapsed:F2}ms (budget: {budget}ms)");
        }
    }
}
```

### Layout Budget (Target: <3ms)

```csharp
public class LayoutBudget
{
    // Per-view budgets
    public const double SimpleView = 0.1;    // Label, BoxView, Image
    public const double LayoutView = 0.5;    // Grid, StackLayout
    public const double ComplexView = 1.0;   // CollectionView, WebView

