## Budget Enforcement

Implement automatic budget validation:

```csharp
public class PerformanceBudgetValidator
{
    private readonly Dictionary<string, List<double>> _measurements = new();

    public void RecordMeasurement(string operation, double milliseconds, double budget)
    {
        if (!_measurements.ContainsKey(operation))
        {
            _measurements[operation] = new List<double>();
        }

        _measurements[operation].Add(milliseconds);

        if (milliseconds > budget)
        {
            OnBudgetExceeded(operation, milliseconds, budget);
        }
    }

    private void OnBudgetExceeded(string operation, double actual, double budget)
    {
        var overage = ((actual - budget) / budget) * 100;

        Debug.WriteLine($"⚠️ BUDGET EXCEEDED: {operation}");
        Debug.WriteLine($"   Actual: {actual:F2}ms");
        Debug.WriteLine($"   Budget: {budget:F2}ms");
        Debug.WriteLine($"   Overage: {overage:F1}%");

        // In debug builds, throw to fail tests
        #if DEBUG
        if (overage > 50) // More than 50% over budget
        {
            throw new PerformanceException($"{operation} exceeded budget by {overage:F1}%");
        }
        #endif
    }

    public BudgetReport GenerateReport()
    {
        var report = new BudgetReport();

        foreach (var kvp in _measurements)
        {
            var measurements = kvp.Value;
            report.Operations.Add(new OperationReport
            {
                Name = kvp.Key,
                Average = measurements.Average(),
                P95 = Percentile(measurements, 0.95),
                P99 = Percentile(measurements, 0.99),
                Max = measurements.Max(),
                Violations = measurements.Count(m => m > GetBudget(kvp.Key))
            });
        }

        return report;
    }
}
```

## Performance Budget Checklist

Before releasing, verify:

- ✅ **Frame time P95 < 16.67ms**: 95% of frames render within budget
- ✅ **Frame time P99 < 25ms**: Even worst-case frames are acceptable
- ✅ **Layout time < 3ms**: Fast measure/arrange cycles
- ✅ **Render time < 8ms**: Efficient Skia drawing
- ✅ **Allocation rate < 1MB/sec**: Minimal GC pressure
- ✅ **Cold start < 2 seconds**: Fast application launch
- ✅ **Page transitions < 300ms**: Smooth navigation
- ✅ **Memory footprint < 250MB**: Reasonable resource usage

These budgets ensure your OpenMaui application delivers a premium desktop experience on Linux.

