## Case Study 2: Dashboard with Heavy Animations

### Problem

A dashboard with real-time charts and animations dropped to 30 FPS during updates.

### Investigation

```csharp
// Initial implementation - JANKY
public class DashboardPage : ContentPage
{
    private Timer _updateTimer;

    public DashboardPage()
    {
        var chart = new ChartView();
        var statsGrid = new Grid();
        // ... setup UI ...

        // ❌ BAD: Updates on UI thread every 100ms
        _updateTimer = new Timer(_ =>
        {
            Dispatcher.Dispatch(() =>
            {
                UpdateChartData();
                UpdateStatistics();
                AnimateChanges();
            });
        }, null, 0, 100);
    }

    private void UpdateChartData()
    {
        // ❌ BAD: Expensive calculation on UI thread
        var data = CalculateChartData(); // Takes 8ms
        chart.Data = data;
    }
}
```

Profiling revealed:
- Chart calculation: **8ms** on UI thread
- Unnecessary full redraws: **12ms** per update
- 10 updates/second = only 6.67ms available per frame

### Solution

```csharp
// Optimized implementation - SMOOTH
public class DashboardPage : ContentPage
{
    private Timer _updateTimer;
    private readonly SemaphoreSlim _updateLock = new(1, 1);

    public DashboardPage()
    {
        var chart = new ChartView
        {
            // ✅ GOOD: Enable render caching
            EnableRenderCache = true
        };

        // ✅ GOOD: Throttle updates to 60 FPS max
        _updateTimer = new Timer(_ => UpdateDataAsync(), null, 0, 16);
    }

    private async void UpdateDataAsync()
    {
        // ✅ GOOD: Prevent overlapping updates
        if (!await _updateLock.WaitAsync(0))
            return;

        try
        {
            // ✅ GOOD: Calculate on background thread
            var data = await Task.Run(() => CalculateChartData());

            // ✅ GOOD: Only update if data changed
            if (!data.Equals(_lastData))
            {
                await Dispatcher.DispatchAsync(() =>
                {
                    chart.Data = data;
                    chart.InvalidateCache(); // Trigger re-render
                });

                _lastData = data;
            }
        }
        finally
        {
            _updateLock.Release();
        }
    }
}

public class ChartView : GraphicsView
{
    private ChartData? _data;

    public ChartData? Data
    {
        get => _data;
        set
        {
            if (_data?.Equals(value) == true)
                return; // Skip if unchanged

            _data = value;

            // ✅ GOOD: Animate smoothly
            this.AbortAnimation("ChartUpdate");
            this.Animate("ChartUpdate", 
                callback: v => Invalidate(),
                length: 250,
                easing: Easing.CubicOut);
        }
    }
}
```

### Results

- Chart calculation: Moved to background thread (0ms UI thread impact)
- Frame time: **14ms** average, **18ms** P99
- Consistent 60 FPS during updates
- CPU usage: **35%** → **18%**

## Case Study 3: Image Gallery Memory Leak

### Problem

An image gallery app's memory usage grew from 80MB to 800MB after viewing 100 images, eventually crashing.

### Investigation

```csharp
