## Case Study 2: Dashboard with Heavy Animations

### Problem

A dashboard with real-time charts and animations dropped to 30 FPS during updates.

### Investigation

```csharp
// Initial implementation - JANKY
public class DashboardPage : ContentPage
{
    private Timer _updateTimer;

    public DashboardPage()
    {
        var chart = new ChartView();
        var statsGrid = new Grid();
        // ... setup UI ...

        // ❌ BAD: Updates on UI thread every 100ms
        _updateTimer = new Timer(_ =>
        {
            Dispatcher.Dispatch(() =>
            {
                UpdateChartData();
                UpdateStatistics();
                AnimateChanges();
            });
        }, null, 0, 100);
    }

    private void UpdateChartData()
    {
        // ❌ BAD: Expensive calculation on UI thread
        var data = CalculateChartData(); // Takes 8ms
        chart.Data = data;
    }
}
```

Profiling revealed:
- Chart calculation: **8ms** on UI thread
- Unnecessary full redraws: **12ms** per update
- 10 updates/second = only 6.67ms available per frame

### Solution

```csharp
// Optimized implementation - SMOOTH
public class DashboardPage : ContentPage
{
    private Timer _updateTimer;
    private readonly SemaphoreSlim _updateLock = new(1, 1);

    public DashboardPage()
    {
        var chart = new ChartView
        {
            // ✅ GOOD: Enable render caching
            EnableRenderCache = true
        };

        // ✅ GOOD: Throttle updates to 60 FPS max
        _updateTimer = new Timer(_ => UpdateDataAsync(), null, 0, 16);
    }

    private async void UpdateDataAsync()
    {
        // ✅ GOOD: Prevent overlapping updates
        if (!await _updateLock.WaitAsync(0))
            return;

        try
        {
            // ✅ GOOD: Calculate on background thread
            var data = await Task.Run(() => CalculateChartData());

            // ✅ GOOD: Only update if data changed
            if (!data.Equals(_lastData))
            {
                await Dispatcher.DispatchAsync(() =>
                {
                    chart.Data = data;
                    chart.InvalidateCache(); // Trigger re-render
                });

                _lastData = data;
            }
        }
        finally
        {
            _updateLock.Release();
        }
    }
}

public class ChartView : GraphicsView
{
    private ChartData? _data;

    public ChartData? Data
    {
        get => _data;
        set
        {
            if (_data?.Equals(value) == true)
                return; // Skip if unchanged

            _data = value;

            // ✅ GOOD: Animate smoothly
            this.AbortAnimation("ChartUpdate");
            this.Animate("ChartUpdate", 
                callback: v => Invalidate(),
                length: 250,
                easing: Easing.CubicOut);
        }
    }
}
```

### Results

- Chart calculation: Moved to background thread (0ms UI thread impact)
- Frame time: **14ms** average, **18ms** P99
- Consistent 60 FPS during updates
- CPU usage: **35%** → **18%**

## Case Study 3: Image Gallery Memory Leak

### Problem

An image gallery app's memory usage grew from 80MB to 800MB after viewing 100 images, eventually crashing.

### Investigation

```csharp
// Initial implementation - LEAKY
public class GalleryPage : ContentPage
{
    public GalleryPage()
    {
        var carousel = new CarouselView
        {
            ItemsSource = ImageService.GetAllImages(), // 1000+ images
            ItemTemplate = new DataTemplate(() =>
            {
                var image = new Image { Aspect = Aspect.AspectFit };
                image.SetBinding(Image.SourceProperty, "FullResolutionUrl");

                // ❌ BAD: No disposal, loads full resolution
                return image;
            })
        };

        Content = carousel;
    }
}
```

Memory profiling showed:
- Each image: **8-12MB** (4K resolution)
- Images never released from memory
- No cache size limits

### Solution

```csharp
// Optimized implementation - EFFICIENT
public class GalleryPage : ContentPage
{
    public GalleryPage()
    {
        var carousel = new CarouselView
        {
            ItemsSource = ImageService.GetAllImages(),
            Loop = false, // ✅ GOOD: Reduce buffering
            PeekAreaInsets = 0,
            ItemTemplate = new DataTemplate(typeof(OptimizedImageView))
        };

        Content = carousel;
    }
}

public class OptimizedImageView : ContentView
{
    private Image _image;
    private CancellationTokenSource? _loadCts;

    public OptimizedImageView()
    {
        _image = new Image 
        { 
            Aspect = Aspect.AspectFit,
            // ✅ GOOD: Limit size to screen dimensions
            WidthRequest = 1920,
            HeightRequest = 1080
        };

        Content = _image;
    }

    protected override void OnBindingContextChanged()
    {
        base.OnBindingContextChanged();

        // ✅ GOOD: Cancel previous load
        _loadCts?.Cancel();
        _loadCts = new CancellationTokenSource();

        if (BindingContext is ImageInfo imageInfo)
        {
            LoadImageAsync(imageInfo, _loadCts.Token);
        }
    }

    private async void LoadImageAsync(ImageInfo imageInfo, CancellationToken ct)
    {
        try
        {
            // ✅ GOOD: Load appropriate resolution
            var source = await ImageService.GetOptimizedImageAsync(
                imageInfo.Url, 
                maxWidth: 1920, 
                maxHeight: 1080,
                ct);

            if (!ct.IsCancellationRequested)
            {
                _image.Source = source;
            }
        }
        catch (OperationCanceledException)
        {
            // Expected when scrolling quickly
        }
    }

    // ✅ GOOD: Clean up when view is recycled
    protected override void OnDisappearing()
    {
        base.OnDisappearing();
        _loadCts?.Cancel();
        _image.Source = null; // Release bitmap
    }
}

public static class ImageService
{
    private static readonly LRUCache<string, ImageSource> _cache = new(maxSize: 50);

    public static async Task<ImageSource> GetOptimizedImageAsync(
        string url, int maxWidth, int maxHeight, CancellationToken ct)
    {
        if (_cache.TryGetValue(url, out var cached))
            return cached;

        // ✅ GOOD: Resize on load
        var bitmap = await LoadAndResizeAsync(url, maxWidth, maxHeight, ct);
        var source = ImageSource.FromStream(() => bitmap);

        _cache.Add(url, source);
        return source;
    }
}
```

### Results

- Memory usage: **800MB** → **120MB** (85% reduction)
- Peak memory: **150MB** (stable)
- Image load time: **180ms** → **45ms** (smaller images)
- No more crashes

## Key Takeaways

1. **Profile before optimizing**: Measure to identify real bottlenecks
2. **Apply budgets**: Use concrete targets for each operation
3. **Virtualize collections**: Essential for large datasets
4. **Cache strategically**: Balance performance vs. memory
5. **Dispose properly**: Prevent leaks in long-running apps
6. **Offload work**: Keep UI thread responsive
7. **Test on target hardware**: Linux systems vary widely in capabilities

These optimization patterns apply across OpenMaui applications, ensuring smooth 60 FPS performance on Linux desktop platforms.
